# Payments Domain – Ubiquitous Language

# Purpose

This document defines the shared vocabulary used across the Payments Domain. It ensures that business stakeholders, engineers, and downstream systems use consistent terminology when describing payment concepts, workflows, and states.

All terms defined here are authoritative within the Payments Domain context.

---

# Core Payment Terms

| Term                | Definition                                                                               | Context                                                                        |
| ------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| Payment             | A financial transaction initiated by a client to transfer funds from a payer to a payee. | Core domain concept representing the end-to-end transaction lifecycle.         |
| Payment Request     | A request to initiate a payment process.                                                 | Input from upstream systems such as Orders or Billing.                         |
| Payment Intent      | A preliminary representation of a payment before execution.                              | Used when payment confirmation or authorization is required before processing. |
| Payment Transaction | The concrete execution instance of a payment with a provider.                            | Represents interaction with external payment providers.                        |
| Payment Status      | The current state of a payment in its lifecycle.                                         | Used for tracking and state transitions.                                       |
| Payment Lifecycle   | The sequence of states a payment goes through from creation to completion or failure.    | Defines allowed state transitions.                                             |

---

# Payment States

| Term       | Definition                                           | Context                                                     |
| ---------- | ---------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------- |
| Initiated  | Payment has been created but not yet processed.      | Initial state after payment creation.                       |
| Pending    | Payment is awaiting processing or confirmation.      | Typically waiting on external provider or async validation. |
| Authorized | Payment has been approved but not yet captured.      | Common in card-based flows.                                 |
| Processing | Payment is actively being processed by a provider.   | Temporary state during execution.                           |
| Completed  | Payment has been successfully processed and settled. | Terminal success state.                                     |
| Failed     | Payment could not be completed due to an error.      | Terminal failure state.                                     |
| Cancelled  | Payment was intentionally aborted before completion. | User or system-initiated cancellation.                      |
| Refunded   | Payment has been reversed partially or fully.        | Post-completion reversal state.                             |

---

# Actors & Roles

| Term             | Definition                                               | Context                                   |
| ---------------- | -------------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------- |
| Client           | The end user or system initiating a payment.             | Originator of payment requests.           |
| Payer            | The entity that provides funds for the payment.          | May differ from client in some scenarios. |
| Payee            | The entity receiving funds from a payment.               | Target beneficiary of payment.            |
| Merchant         | Business entity receiving payment for goods or services. | Common in e-commerce flows.               |
| Payment Provider | External service that processes financial transactions.  | Includes PSPs like Stripe or Adyen.       |

---

# Integration & Systems

| Term                           | Definition                                                              | Context                                 |
| ------------------------------ | ----------------------------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------- |
| Payment Service Provider (PSP) | External system that executes payment processing.                       | Abstracted behind provider adapters.    |
| Payment Gateway                | Interface layer that routes payment requests to providers.              | Internal abstraction layer.             |
| Reconciliation                 | The process of matching internal payment records with provider records. | Ensures financial correctness.          |
| Settlement                     | The transfer of funds from payer to payee via provider systems.         | Final financial transfer stage.         |
| Ledger                         | System of record for financial accounting entries.                      | External accounting system integration. |

---

# Events

| Term              | Definition                                          | Context                                 |
| ----------------- | --------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------- |
| PaymentCreated    | Event emitted when a payment is created.            | Triggered at initialization stage.      |
| PaymentAuthorized | Event emitted when payment is approved.             | Used in approval-based flows.           |
| PaymentProcessed  | Event emitted when provider processing completes.   | Intermediate or final processing event. |
| PaymentCompleted  | Event emitted when payment is successfully settled. | Terminal success event.                 |
| PaymentFailed     | Event emitted when payment processing fails.        | Terminal failure event.                 |
| PaymentRefunded   | Event emitted when a refund is executed.            | Post-settlement reversal event.         |

---

# Operational Terms

| Term                 | Definition                                                                           | Context                                           |
| -------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------- |
| Idempotency          | Property ensuring repeated requests produce the same result without duplication.     | Critical for safe retries in payment APIs.        |
| Reconciliation Batch | Group of transactions processed together for validation.                             | Used in financial matching workflows.             |
| Retry                | Re-attempt of a failed or incomplete operation.                                      | Used in transient failure handling.               |
| Timeout              | Maximum allowed time for a payment operation before marking it as failed or pending. | Operational constraint in provider communication. |
| Audit Trail          | Complete history of actions performed on a payment.                                  | Required for compliance and traceability.         |

---

# Notes

* Terms defined here must be used consistently in all domain documentation.
* Any new term introduced in design, code, or events must be added here or rejected during review.
* Conflicting terminology across domains should be resolved at the bounded context level.
